directory: crates/ctx-context
domain: Crate providing the ctx-context CLI/hook tool: computes and renders the rollup/intent/leaf context chain above any repo path, and injects unseen chain content into Claude Code sessions via a fail-open PostToolUse hook. Distributed as both a binary (`main.rs`) and a library (`lib.rs`) built from the same `src/` module set, verified by an independent in-memory integration test suite.
edit_notes:
  - Changes to chain structure/ordering or session ledger path scheme must be mirrored in tests/ (chain_serve.rs, hook_session.rs assert both directly).
  - All real filesystem/env access funnels through `Env`/`StdEnv` (src/env.rs); tests substitute `FakeEnv` and never touch disk.
children:
  - Cargo.toml: manifest — binary+lib crate, clap/thiserror deps, publish=false.
  - src/: implementation — CLI, hook logic, chain computation, rendering, session dedup, path validation, error taxonomy.
  - tests/: black-box behavioral tests against FakeEnv covering chain order, absence handling, path-escape rejection, and hook/session dedup.
invariants:
  - Hook-mode paths never fail the calling process; errors degrade to empty/marker output (fail-open).
  - Only .context/ scaffolding (rollup.ctx, intent.md, leaf .ctx) content is ever served — source file bytes never flow through serve/hook.
  - All cross-module errors are `CtxError`; no anyhow/dyn-Error boxing anywhere in the crate.